transform_def.name: designed_3rd16
transform_def.string: let r = 1 / length(p_in) r1 = 2 / length(p_in) r2 = 0.5 / length(p_in) a1 = sin(length(p_in) + cos(abs(p_in.x))) a2 = cos(length(p_in) + sin(abs(p_in.x))) a = clamp(a1, a2, sin(abs(p_in.x) + abs(p_in.y))) b = exp(sin(abs(p_in.x))) c = (abs(p_in.x) + abs(p_in.y)) * invpi() z = if r < c * invpi() then fmod(c, fmod(b, a)) else fmod(b / a - c, p_in.x) / tanh(p_in.x) con0 = abs(z) > r1 con1 = abs(z) < r1 && abs(z) > r2 con2 = abs(z) < r2 in (if if fill <= 0.0 then con0 else if fill > 0.25 then con2 else con1 then p_in else vec2(0.0)) * weight
